Morals

I've been dabbling into the strange world of morals and ethics during these few months. After reading the Subtle Art of Not Giving A F*** and WINNING WITH HONOR, I felt that there were valuable moral lessons that are worth sharing to others.

1. Entitlement
A big theme of morals involve the feeling of entitlement. Simply put, it means the idea that we deserve something (usually positive) without putting in the required amount of effort into it. I admit that I was an entitled teenager as I always felt the need to feel positive and accomodating to others. As a result, I sometimes felt bad (and felt bad about feeling bad) and lost my sense of identity as I was too agreeable. I learnt that it is entirely okay to feel bad about feeling bad as it is only human and that it is okay to say "NO!" in order to establish boundaries with other people.

2. Failures
Another big theme present in both books is one's attitude towards failures. It encourages readers to adopt a positive attitude towards failures. I've always adopted this stance towards failures in nearly all aspects of my life. I've always felt that I learnt more and faster from my failures than my successes. Hence, I owe all my successes to my failures.

3. Happiness is not the goal
Another core theme in the books is the constant emphasis that doing something to become happy is in itself, self-defeating. Instead, the books challenges the readers to choose the problems they are willing to struggle for, and in solving these problems come fulfillment and ultimately, happiness. In Winning with Honor, the book strongly emphasizes on the highest need on the Maslow's Triangle: Transcendence - the ability to help others reach their highest potential. I admit that I've not been actively helping people reach their highest potential, but rather focusing alot in solving my own personal problems. I feel that having a balance of the 2 would be much more favourable.

In conclusion, I've learnt that when it comes to morals, it is better to keep things stupidly simple but practice strict adherence to your values. With that, I wish the readers good luck in constructing their moral framework.
